Chapter 2: Anatomy of a Volume Candle

30
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:45,360
A volume candle holds seven critical parts 
that tell the full story of price movement. 

31
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:50,640
Let’s break down each element and 
show you how they work together.
  

32
00:02:50,640 --> 00:02:57,120
Every volume candle has an open price, which 
marks where trading started in that time period. 

33
00:02:57,120 --> 00:03:05,120
For green candles, you find this at the bottom 
of the body. For red candles, it sits at the top. 

34
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:10,400
This starting point sets the stage for 
the battle between buyers and sellers.
  

35
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:15,520
The high price shows the maximum point 
buyers pushed during that period. 

36
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:22,000
You see this at the top of the upper wick. This 
tells you how far buyers managed to drive prices  

37
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:28,400
up, even if they couldn't hold those levels.
The low price, marked by the bottom of  

38
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:33,760
the lower wick, reveals the lowest 
point where sellers drove the price. 

39
00:03:33,760 --> 00:03:38,880
These extreme points show you the full 
range of the price battle that happened.
  

40
00:03:38,880 --> 00:03:44,960
The close price tells you who won that 
period's battle - buyers or sellers. 

41
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:50,800
On green candles, you find it at the 
top of the body, showing buyers won. 

42
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:56,400
On red candles, it's at the bottom, 
meaning sellers took control.
  

43
00:03:56,400 --> 00:04:02,800
The upper wick, that line sticking up from 
the body, shows rejection of higher prices. 

44
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:08,080
A long upper wick means buyers 
tried pushing up, but failed. 

45
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:13,280
No upper wick signals strong buying 
pressure, that held through the close. 

46
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:18,800
A long lower wick reveals sellers 
tried pushing down, but failed. 

47
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:24,640
When you see no lower wick, sellers 
maintained control throughout the period.
  

48
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:28,720
The candle body, the thick 
part between open and close,  

49
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:36,800
shows who won the period and by how much. A wide 
body means strong conviction in that direction. 

50
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:41,920
A narrow body points to weak 
conviction or indecision.
  

51
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:46,960
Now, what makes volume candles 
special is their width variation. 

52
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:51,680
Unlike regular candles that stay 
the same width, volume candles grow  

53
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:59,680
wider or narrower based on trading activity.
This adds a vital dimension to your analysis.
  

54
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:04,960
Wide candles mean heavy trading volume, 
lots of buyers and sellers fought  

55
00:05:04,960 --> 00:05:10,640
over prices during that period.
Narrow candles show light volume,  

56
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:15,760
fewer traders participated.
This width variation reveals  

57
00:05:15,760 --> 00:05:20,320
trading intensity at a glance.
 
The relationship between candle  

58
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:25,760
parts tells deeper stories.
Take a wide candle with no wicks.  

59
00:05:25,760 --> 00:05:30,960
This shows strong agreement on price 
direction with heavy participation. 
  

60
00:05:30,960 --> 00:05:35,280
But how about a wide candle 
with long wicks! That reveals  

61
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:42,800
intense fighting between buyers and sellers.
 
Watch how the candle width changes as price moves. 

62
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:48,000
Increasing width during price 
rises shows growing buyer strength. 

63
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:54,480
But if the width starts shrinking while price 
still rises, buyers might be losing steam.
  

64
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:59,440
The open and close positions relative 
to the total range matter too. 

65
00:05:59,440 --> 00:06:06,560
A close near the high with wide volume suggests 
strong buying pressure likely to continue. 

66
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:12,880
A close far from the extremes with 
high volume might signal indecision.
  

67
00:06:12,880 --> 00:06:20,480
Some traders focus only on candle colors or 
patterns. But volume width adds crucial context. 

68
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:28,400
A tiny green candle with huge volume, might mean 
more than a large red candle with thin volume.
  

69
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:34,320
Pay special attention to how volume 
width changes around key price levels. 

70
00:06:34,320 --> 00:06:40,400
A surge in width near support or resistance 
often signals important market decisions  

71
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:45,440
happening. We’ll talk about this later.
The real power comes from reading  

72
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:49,520
all these elements together.
Each part adds to the story,  

73
00:06:49,520 --> 00:06:55,520
but the volume width ties it all together by 
showing the conviction behind every move.
  

74
00:06:55,520 --> 00:07:00,720
The beauty of volume candles lies in 
their ability to show both price action,  

75
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:07,760
and trading intensity, in one clean visual.
This complete picture helps you make faster,  

76
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:10,800
more accurate trading decisions.
 
Chapter 3: Understanding Price Movement Flow

77
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:16,240
Stop looking at single candles, and start 
seeing the market as a flowing story,  

78
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:22,880
where each candle connects to the next.
A green candle might signal buying, but its true  

79
00:07:22,880 --> 00:07:29,920
