Volume patterns tell deeper  

132
00:12:21,920 --> 00:12:29,120
stories. Rising price with falling volume, 
meaning thinner candles, warns of weakness. 

133
00:12:29,120 --> 00:12:35,680
Falling price with rising volume, meaning 
wider candles, shows real selling pressure. 

134
00:12:35,680 --> 00:12:42,080
These volume shifts often signal important 
trend changes, before price confirms them.
 

135
00:12:42,080 --> 00:12:46,000
Always remember that smart 
money leaves traces in volume. 

136
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:50,800
They can't hide their large trades. 
When you see wide volume candles,  

137
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:56,800
with small price moves, big players might 
be quietly accumulating or distributing. 

138
00:12:56,800 --> 00:13:02,560
These volume hints reveal their plans.
 
I repeat, price action can lie,  

139
00:13:02,560 --> 00:13:08,480
but volume tells truth.
Market makers can push price around temporarily,  

140
00:13:08,480 --> 00:13:14,640
but they can't fake real trading activity.
This makes volume candles one of the most  

141
00:13:14,640 --> 00:13:23,280
reliable tools for spotting genuine market moves.
 
And watch how volume reacts at key price levels. 

142
00:13:23,280 --> 00:13:28,400
Strong support or resistance needs 
strong volume candles to break. 

143
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:33,680
Thin volume candles at these levels often 
means the break will fail, no matter how  

144
00:13:33,680 --> 00:13:38,480
