A break with thin candles raises doubts.
Look for wide candles pushing through the level,  

205
00:19:10,800 --> 00:19:17,600
showing real selling pressure. The width of the 
candles tells you if sellers mean business.
  

206
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:21,120
Market structure changes 
show through candle patterns. 

207
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:26,320
A series of wide candles breaking a 
trend line, or a key structure level,  

208
00:19:26,320 --> 00:19:30,880
carries more weight than thin ones.
The width shows conviction in the  

209
00:19:30,880 --> 00:19:33,600
structural change.
 
Price congestion  

210
00:19:33,600 --> 00:19:41,040
zones create their own key levels.
Notice how candle width changes in these areas. 

211
00:19:41,040 --> 00:19:46,400
Wide candles pushing into congestion 
often fail, while patient accumulation  

212
00:19:46,400 --> 00:19:53,280
with thinner candles might succeed.
 
The character of candles shifts at major levels. 

213
00:19:53,280 --> 00:19:59,120
A trend of steady wide candles might turn 
into erratic thin ones at resistance. 

214
00:19:59,120 --> 00:20:06,480
This change warns of possible trend exhaustion.
False breakouts often start with thin candles.  

215
00:20:06,480 --> 00:20:13,280
Even if price moves beyond the level, narrow 
candle width suggests lack of commitment. 

216
00:20:13,280 --> 00:20:17,280
So wait for wide candles 
to confirm the real break.
  

217
00:20:17,280 --> 00:20:24,320
Volume candle width helps spot distribution tops.
At resistance, rising price with shrinking candle  

218
00:20:24,320 --> 00:20:30,880
width warns of weakness. Big players 
might be quietly selling into the move.
  

219
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:37,280
Support and resistance lose strength with each 
test. But watch how candle width evolves during  

220
00:20:37,280 --> 00:20:44,640
retests. Widening candles show growing interest.
 
Some levels hold special weight - like  

221
00:20:44,640 --> 00:20:48,800
weekly highs or lows.
Expect wider candles at  

222
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:55,920
these points, as more traders watch them.
Thin candles at major levels often precede  

223
00:20:55,920 --> 00:20:59,040
violent moves.
 
Market memory  

224
00:20:59,040 --> 00:21:05,200
also creates support from old resistance.
When price returns to these flipped levels,  

225
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:13,040
compare current candle width to previous tests.
Similar patterns often produce similar results.
  

226
00:21:13,040 --> 00:21:18,960
The stopping volume pattern shows as a 
single wide candle. It appears at key levels,  

227
00:21:18,960 --> 00:21:24,400
often with a long wick. This candle 
type signals strong rejection.
  

228
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:28,240
Price congestion creates 
natural support and resistance. 

229
00:21:28,240 --> 00:21:34,080
Study how candle width changes when 
price enters and exits these zones. 

230
00:21:34,080 --> 00:21:38,720
Wide candles leaving congestion 
often start strong trends.
  

231
00:21:39,280 --> 00:21:45,280
Momentum loss shows through candle width changes.
As price approaches resistance,  

232
00:21:45,280 --> 00:21:52,080
watch if candles get thinner.
This gradual weakening often precedes reversals.
  

233
00:21:52,080 --> 00:21:55,760
Supply and demand balance 
shows in candle patterns. 

234
00:21:55,760 --> 00:22:01,680
Wide candles mean strong imbalance, 
thin candles suggest equilibrium. 

235
00:22:01,680 --> 00:22:06,000
Key levels often flip when this 
balance shifts dramatically.
 
  

236
00:22:06,560 --> 00:22:12,480
Time frames affect how you read candle width.
A wide candle on a daily chart carries  

237
00:22:12,480 --> 00:22:19,440
more weight than on a 5-minute chart.
So match your analysis to your trading timeframe.
  

238
00:22:19,440 --> 00:22:25,040
The market structure creates its own 
key points through swing highs and lows. 

239
00:22:25,040 --> 00:22:29,360
Watch how candle width behaves 
at these natural levels. 

240
00:22:29,360 --> 00:22:33,520
They often work as well as 
traditional support and resistance.
  

241
00:22:33,520 --> 00:22:39,680
I hope you see how price action becomes 
more reliable when candle width confirms it. 

242
00:22:39,680 --> 00:22:45,520
A resistance break with wide candles 
and high volume shows conviction. 

243
00:22:45,520 --> 00:22:46,480
The same break with  

244
00:22:46,480 --> 00:22:50,560
thin candles might trap traders.
 
Chapter 7: Entry and Exit Triggers

245
00:22:50,560 --> 00:22:55,520
Volume candles give clear signals 
for entering and exiting trades. 

246
00:22:55,520 --> 00:23:00,000
I said it before, wide candles 
show strong market commitment. 

247
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:04,960
But when a wide green candle engulfs 
several previous red candles, this  

248
00:23:04,960 --> 00:23:09,280
signals potential buying pressure.
The opposite happens when a wide  

249
00:23:09,280 --> 00:23:16,880
red candle swallows prior green ones.
 
Pin bars with extra width need special attention. 

250
00:23:16,880 --> 00:23:21,680
A pin bar is like a rejection stick 
- when it's wider than surrounding  

251
00:23:21,680 --> 00:23:29,520
candles, the rejection carries more weight.
Look for these wide pin bars at key price levels,  

252
00:23:29,520 --> 00:23:34,480
especially if they come with high volume.
 
Entry timing improves by watching  

253
00:23:34,480 --> 00:23:39,280
the candle width progression.
If candles get progressively wider  

254
00:23:39,280 --> 00:23:45,760
during a move, it shows building momentum.
This often leads to stronger trends. The  

255
00:23:45,760 --> 00:23:53,120
width increase confirms price direction.
 
Exit signals often appear as reversal candles. 

256
00:23:53,120 --> 00:23:59,520
When a strong trend shows wide candles in one 
direction, watch for an opposing wide candle  

257
00:23:59,520 --> 00:24:04,240
to signal potential reversal.
The wider the reversal candle,  

258
00:24:04,240 --> 00:24:08,640
the stronger the signal.
Of course, false signals need  

259
00:24:08,640 --> 00:24:15,200
filtering. Not every wide candle means action.
Look for confirmation from surrounding price  

260
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:20,640
action and volume patterns. Single 
candles rarely tell the whole story.
  

261
00:24:21,200 --> 00:24:26,800
Time of day affects candle width 
interpretation. Market opens or closes  

262
00:24:26,800 --> 00:24:34,000
often show wider candles. These times need 
different analysis than mid-session trading. 

263
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:40,000
The first hour of trading deserves special 
study. Wide candles during this time often  

264
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:46,400
set the day's tone. But be careful - 
early moves sometimes reverse quickly.
  

265
00:24:46,400 --> 00:24:53,280
Risk management also links to candle width.
Wider candles often mean more volatility,  

266
00:24:53,280 --> 00:24:57,360
suggesting wider stops.
Adjust position size  

267
00:24:57,360 --> 00:25:05,040
accordingly to maintain consistent risk levels.
 
Trend confirmation uses candle width patterns. 

268
00:25:05,040 --> 00:25:10,960
A sequence of widening candles in the 
trend direction supports continuation. 

269
00:25:10,960 --> 00:25:17,440
Thinning candles might warn of weakness.
 
Price gaps between candles need attention. 

270
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:24,080
Wide candles after gaps often signal continuation.
But watch for reversal patterns if  

271
00:25:24,080 --> 00:25:30,480
volume doesn't confirm the move.
 
Counter-trend signals need extra confirmation. 

272
00:25:30,480 --> 00:25:35,120
A wide reversal candle against 
the main trend needs more support,  

273
00:25:35,120 --> 00:25:40,880
than one moving with the trend.
Pattern recognition improves with practice.  

274
00:25:40,880 --> 00:25:47,040
Start by marking wide candles on your charts.
Notice how they cluster at important  

275
00:25:47,040 --> 00:25:52,880
points and what follows them.
 
My go-to signals using volume candles  

276
00:25:52,880 --> 00:25:58,880
include engulfing candles and pin bars.
A bullish engulfing candle happens when  

277
00:25:58,880 --> 00:26:04,160
a green candle completely covers the 
body of the previous red candle. This  

278
00:26:04,160 --> 00:26:10,320
shows buyers taking control with force.
 
The real power comes from volume analysis. 

279
00:26:10,320 --> 00:26:18,320
Here, you see a bearish trend with several small 
red candles. Then suddenly, a large green candle  

280
00:26:18,320 --> 00:26:26,640
appears, with volume much higher than the average.
This green giant engulfs previous red candles.  

281
00:26:26,640 --> 00:26:32,720
That's not just a reversal signal, it's a 
strong sign of smart money stepping in.
  

282
00:26:32,720 --> 00:26:37,280
Volume candles tells if the 
engulfing move is real or fake. 

283
00:26:37,280 --> 00:26:43,440
Small candles with low volume, followed by 
a wide engulfing candle with high volume,  

284
00:26:43,440 --> 00:26:47,600
shows real buying pressure.
Smart money likes to move prices  

285
00:26:47,600 --> 00:26:53,440
when other traders least expect it.
 
A pin bar looks like a hammer - it  

286
00:26:53,440 --> 00:26:58,480
has a long wick and short body.
But volume makes some pin bars  

287
00:26:58,480 --> 00:27:02,400
more special than others.
A pin bar with much higher  

288
00:27:02,400 --> 00:27:09,280
volume carries more weight than regular ones.
It shows strong rejection of a price level.
  

289
00:27:09,280 --> 00:27:15,600
Take this example: The price drops for 
several candles, with thin red candles. 

290
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:23,040
And right here, you see a big pin bar - wider 
than the previous candles, with a long lower wick. 

291
00:27:23,040 --> 00:27:28,880
The volume on this pin bar is higher 
than normal. This isn't just a pin bar,  

292
00:27:28,880 --> 00:27:33,360
it's smart money entering.
 
You see, professional traders  

293
00:27:33,360 --> 00:27:38,880
don't just look at candle body size.
They combine it with volume study. 

294
00:27:38,880 --> 00:27:47,920
A thin pin bar with low volume might be a trap. 
But high volume confirms real market intent.
  

295
00:27:47,920 --> 00:27:53,520
During consolidation, you might see 
small candles with average volume. 

296
00:27:53,520 --> 00:27:59,200
Then breaks out with a wide engulfing 
candle and big volume. This shows  

297
00:27:59,200 --> 00:28:06,240
institutional players making their move.
 
Volume shifts during the day matter too. 

298
00:28:06,240 --> 00:28:12,560
An engulfing pattern at market open needs 
different volume than one at mid-day. 

299
00:28:12,560 --> 00:28:18,880
Morning sessions often have naturally higher 
volume, so adjust your expectations.
 
  

300
00:28:18,880 --> 00:28:22,880
Remember older price zones 
when studying these patterns. 

301
00:28:22,880 --> 00:28:29,920
A pin bar at previous support, showing higher 
width and volume, carries extra significance.  

302
00:28:29,920 --> 00:28:35,600
The market remembers these levels.
A wide red pin bar with high volume,  

303
00:28:35,600 --> 00:28:42,240
at resistance, often signals selling pressure.
The opposite happens at support - green  

304
00:28:42,240 --> 00:28:49,280
pin bars with volume can mark bottoms.
 
Several narrow candles followed by a wide  

305
00:28:49,280 --> 00:28:57,520
engulfing one shows building pressure. If volume 
rises with each candle, the signal gets stronger. 

306
00:28:57,520 --> 00:29:05,280
Narrow candles with low volume followed by a 
wide engulfing candle often trap retail traders. 

307
00:29:05,280 --> 00:29:12,160
So look for volume spikes with engulfing patterns.
A bullish engulfing candle erasing three prior red  

308
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:17,680
candles shows control shifting.
This move could be significant. 

309
00:29:17,680 --> 00:29:25,040
These setups often lead to sustained trends. 
 
 
Wide candles engulfing multiple prior bars show  

310
00:29:25,040 --> 00:29:27,920
decisive action.
And of course,  

311
00:29:27,920 --> 00:29:33,520
pattern recognition improves with practice.
